verse.lines:
Forward my warriors, Hark to the horn;
we go forth to fight and to die.
Be still sweet lady, 'tis not time to mourn;
for the white stag, he yet marches high!
Forward my spearmen, I stand with the shield.
Forward my swordsmen, I call.
To this angry horde, we never shall yield;
though to the last man, this day we may fall.
